{
  "texts": [
    "In our case, topics has been learned from the entire collection of papers, grouping individual papers with a shared subject into the same cluster.",
    "In a broader sense, each topic is formed by the amalgamation of all the papers within the same cluster (i.e., all the journal subprofiles associated with this topic).",
    "For instance, Topic 56 and Topic 60 (in Fig. 3) are addressed in a total of 410 and 257 journals, respectively, with quite different scopes.",
    "Thus, selecting the most significant terms from this amalgamation to describe a topic, i.e., utilizing the entire collection, might not contribute effectively to the understanding of our recommendations.",
    "This is because the resulting description can lead to a significant deviation from the context of our target research paper, making it challenging for the user to discern its relevance."
  ]
}